  "_meta": {
    "description": "Cross-reference between OpenFGA permission scopes, Management API endpoints, and MCP tools. scopes: scope -> what it authorizes. endpoints: endpoint -> ALL scopes it requires. mcp_tools: tool -> ALL scopes it requires.",
    "generated_from": {
      "scopes": "openfga/model/supabase.fga (type scope relations)",
      "endpoints": "api/apps/mgmt-api/specs/v1.spec.json and v2.spec.json — fga_permissions security entries emitted by the @AuthWithFgaPermissions decorator (platform/system endpoints intentionally excluded)",
      "mcp_tools": "@supabase/mcp-server-supabase@0.8.1 tools (served at POST /mcp), mapped to the FGA permission of the equivalent management API operation each tool performs"
    },
    "notes": [
      "Scope lists on endpoints and mcp_tools are conjunctive: the caller needs ALL listed scopes (FgaPermissionsGuard checks every declared permission).",
      "MCP tool authorization is enforced via legacy OAuth scopes (assertMcpOAuthScope) plus ABAC/RLS checks; the FGA permissions shown are the equivalent fine-grained scopes per legacyOauthScopeToFgaPermissionMap and matching v1 endpoints.",
      "MCP tools with no permission scope requirement (search_docs, confirm_cost) and endpoints not guarded by @AuthWithFgaPermissions are not listed.",
      "execute_sql requires only database_read when called with read_only=true; writes require database_read and database_write."
    ]
  },
